This program depends on the ttmath library: https://www.ttmath.org/ It was build with version 0.9.3

Download and extract, place the ttmath/ folder at the root of the repository as reflected in the .gitignore

compile and run with 

make 

OR 

make run

We suggest graph sizes of less that 25 for relatively fast (< 10 minutes) runtimes the combinations part of the code. Comment out the combinations portion before running the bron-kerbosch on larger grpah sizes to see that algorithm work well on larger graphs.

A DEBUG flag exists at the top of main.cpp, enable it to see more verbose output including all the cliques we find and the progress made while checking combinations